the first couple of meetings.

208
00:11:57,771 --> 00:12:01,428
It's not for me. It's for my friend,
Dave. He needs help.

209
00:12:01,596 --> 00:12:03,454
- What are you doing?
- Tell your story.

210
00:12:03,579 --> 00:12:06,516
All right. Welcome, Dave.
Tell us about your love life.

211
00:12:08,406 --> 00:12:11,195
Last summer I was
working in my dad's pub,

212
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:13,387
and this American girl comes in

213
00:12:13,512 --> 00:12:15,609
asking for directions
to Connolly station.

214
00:12:15,777 --> 00:12:18,811
And then she had to go catch
a plane back to New York.

215
00:12:19,588 --> 00:12:20,370
But,

216
00:12:21,393 --> 00:12:23,158
those 20 minutes were all it took.

217
00:12:23,283 --> 00:12:25,083
We... we just had this...

218
00:12:25,845 --> 00:12:28,121
transcendent,
palpable connection.

219
00:12:28,525 --> 00:12:32,292
But unfortunately
I only caught her first name... Holly.

220
00:12:32,799 --> 00:12:36,004
Oh, my God. You're the guy
who changed the ball drop sign.

221
00:12:38,066 --> 00:12:40,971
- With a little bit of help.
- So you know what Dave did?

222
00:12:41,313 --> 00:12:45,305
Dave took all his money,
bought a one-way ticket to New York,

223
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:48,642
and he's been here ever since,
on the streets, on a quest.

224
00:12:48,810 --> 00:12:50,660
So spread the word, people.

225
00:12:50,785 --> 00:12:53,688
If you know a Holly
who had a magic moment

226
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:56,358
with a guy in a pub in Dublin?
He's here.

227
00:12:56,535 --> 00:12:59,986
He's looking for her, and that,
good people, is love!

228
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:06,243
I'm sorry.
That may be romantic, but it's not love.

229
00:13:06,411 --> 00:13:07,246
What?

230
00:13:08,548 --> 00:13:11,111
Didn't you hear him?
"Palpable, transcendent connection"!

231
00:13:11,236 --> 00:13:13,834
Perhaps we can agree
to call it infatuation.

232
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,585
We could agree to disagree.

233
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:19,592
What are you preaching in here...
just don't do it?

234
00:13:20,048 --> 00:13:23,400
- Reach for the copperring?
- I tell people, "be smart."

235
00:13:23,525 --> 00:13:26,179
Love isn't smart.
Love is stupid.

236
00:13:26,627 --> 00:13:29,076
You want to wrestle
that minotaur? Be bold!

237
00:13:29,201 --> 00:13:31,810
Love at first sight is a myth.

238
00:13:32,365 --> 00:13:35,042
Love is built on
a sturdier foundation, Trevor...

239
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:38,066
shared interests,
mutual respect, friendship...

240
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:40,759
things you can't possibly
establish in a couple of days,

241
00:13:40,884 --> 00:13:44,310
- let alone 20 minutes.
- No. Love is passion.

242
00:13:44,993 --> 00:13:47,617
Love is heat, chemistry, sex.

